#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn2:11.1"
msgid "2. Komārabhaccajīvakakathā"
msgstr "A Discussion With Jīvaka Komārabhacca"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:12.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena jīvako komārabhacco rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa "
"vedehiputtassa avidūre tuṇhībhūto nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Jīvaka Komārabhacca was sitting silently not far from the "
"king."

msgctxt "dn2:12.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto jīvakaṃ komārabhaccaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the king said to him:"

msgctxt "dn2:12.3"
msgid "“tvaṃ pana, samma jīvaka, kiṃ tuṇhī”ti?"
msgstr "“But my dear Jīvaka, why are you silent?”"

msgctxt "dn2:12.4"
msgid ""
"“Ayaṃ, deva, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho amhākaṃ ambavane viharati mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ aḍḍhateḷasehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"“Sire, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is "
"staying in my mango grove together with a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants. "

#. VAR: bhagavantaṃ → bhagavantaṃ gotamaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:12.5"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhagavantaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

msgctxt "dn2:12.6"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfect, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme trainer of people, "
"teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "dn2:12.7"
msgid "Taṃ devo bhagavantaṃ payirupāsatu."
msgstr "Let Your Majesty pay homage to him."

msgctxt "dn2:12.8"
msgid "Appeva nāma devassa bhagavantaṃ payirupāsato cittaṃ pasīdeyyā”ti."
msgstr "Hopefully in so doing your mind will find peace.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:13.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, samma jīvaka, hatthiyānāni kappāpehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, my dear Jīvaka, have the elephants readied.”"

msgctxt "dn2:13.2"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho jīvako komārabhacco rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa "
"vedehiputtassa paṭissuṇitvā pañcamattāni hatthinikāsatāni kappāpetvā rañño "
"ca ārohaṇīyaṃ nāgaṃ, rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa "
"paṭivedesi:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sire,” replied Jīvaka. He had around five hundred female elephants "
"readied, in addition to the king’s bull elephant for riding. Then he "
"informed the king:"

msgctxt "dn2:13.3"
msgid "“kappitāni kho te, deva, hatthiyānāni, yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“The elephants are ready, sire. Please go when you’re ready.”"

# BB has "500 of his women", which implies an extensive harem. But the text doesn't imply that they were "his", nor that they were selected from a larger group. They could have been palace women generally, not necessarily attached to Ajatasattu.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:14.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto pañcasu hatthinikāsatesu "
"paccekā itthiyo āropetvā ārohaṇīyaṃ nāgaṃ abhiruhitvā ukkāsu dhāriyamānāsu "
"rājagahamhā niyyāsi mahaccarājānubhāvena, yena jīvakassa komārabhaccassa "
"ambavanaṃ tena pāyāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then King Ajātasattu had women mounted on each of the five hundred female "
"elephants, while he mounted his bull elephant. With attendants carrying "
"torches, he set out in full royal pomp from Rājagaha to Jīvaka’s mango grove."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.50"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:15.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa avidūre ambavanassa "
"ahudeva bhayaṃ, ahu chambhitattaṃ, ahu lomahaṃso."
msgstr ""
"But as he drew near the mango grove, the king became frightened, scared, his "
"hair standing on end."

msgctxt "dn2:15.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhīto saṃviggo lomahaṭṭhajāto "
"jīvakaṃ komārabhaccaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to Jīvaka:"

msgctxt "dn2:15.3"
msgid "“kacci maṃ, samma jīvaka, na vañcesi?"
msgstr "“My dear Jīvaka, I hope you’re not deceiving me!"

msgctxt "dn2:15.4"
msgid "Kacci maṃ, samma jīvaka, na palambhesi?"
msgstr "I hope you’re not betraying me!"

msgctxt "dn2:15.5"
msgid "Kacci maṃ, samma jīvaka, na paccatthikānaṃ desi?"
msgstr "I hope you’re not turning me over to my enemies!"

msgctxt "dn2:15.6"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tāva mahato bhikkhusaṅghassa aḍḍhateḷasānaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ "
"neva khipitasaddo bhavissati, na ukkāsitasaddo na nigghoso”ti."
msgstr ""
"For how on earth can there be no sound of coughing or clearing throats or "
"any noise in such a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:16.1"
msgid "“Mā bhāyi, mahārāja, mā bhāyi, mahārāja."
msgstr "“Do not fear, Great King, do not fear!"

msgctxt "dn2:16.2"
msgid "Na taṃ, deva, vañcemi;"
msgstr "I am not deceiving you,"

msgctxt "dn2:16.3"
msgid "na taṃ, deva, palambhāmi;"
msgstr "or betraying you,"

msgctxt "dn2:16.4"
msgid "na taṃ, deva, paccatthikānaṃ demi."
msgstr "or turning you over to your enemies."

#. VAR: dīpā → padīpā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn2:16.5"
msgid ""
"Abhikkama, mahārāja, abhikkama, mahārāja, ete maṇḍalamāḷe dīpā jhāyantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Go forward, Great King, go forward! Those are lamps shining in the pavilion.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn2:17.1"
msgid "3. Sāmaññaphalapucchā"
msgstr "The Question About the Fruits of the Acetic Life"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
#. VAR: pattikova → padikova (s1) | padiko va (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn2:18.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto yāvatikā nāgassa bhūmi nāgena "
"gantvā, nāgā paccorohitvā, pattikova yena maṇḍalamāḷassa dvāraṃ "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then King Ajātasattu rode on the elephant as far as the terrain allowed, "
"then descended and approached the pavilion door on foot,"

msgctxt "dn2:18.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā jīvakaṃ komārabhaccaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "where he asked Jīvaka:"

msgctxt "dn2:18.3"
msgid "“kahaṃ pana, samma jīvaka, bhagavā”ti?"
msgstr "“But my dear Jīvaka, where is the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "dn2:18.4"
msgid "“Eso, mahārāja, bhagavā;"
msgstr "“That is the Buddha, Great King, that is the Buddha!"

msgctxt "dn2:18.5"
msgid ""
"eso, mahārāja, bhagavā majjhimaṃ thambhaṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisinno "
"purakkhato bhikkhusaṃghassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"He’s sitting against the central column facing east, in front of the Saṅgha "
"of mendicants.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:19.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the king went up to the Buddha"

msgctxt "dn2:19.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "and stood to one side."

msgctxt "dn2:19.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tuṇhībhūtaṃ "
"tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ anuviloketvā rahadamiva vippasannaṃ udānaṃ "
"udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"He looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were so very silent, like a still, "
"clear lake, and spoke these words of inspiration:"

#. VAR: udayabhaddo → udāyibhaddo (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:19.4"
msgid ""
"“iminā me upasamena udayabhaddo kumāro samannāgato hotu, yenetarahi "
"upasamena bhikkhusaṃgho samannāgato”ti."
msgstr ""
"“May my son, Prince Udayabhadda, be blessed with such peace as the Saṅgha of "
"mendicants now enjoys!”"

msgctxt "dn2:19.5"
msgid "“Agamā kho tvaṃ, mahārāja, yathāpeman”ti."
msgstr "“Has your mind gone to one you love, Great King?”"

msgctxt "dn2:19.6"
msgid "“Piyo me, bhante, udayabhaddo kumāro."
msgstr "“I love my son, sir, Prince Udayabhadda."

msgctxt "dn2:19.7"
msgid ""
"Iminā me, bhante, upasamena udayabhaddo kumāro samannāgato hotu yenetarahi "
"upasamena bhikkhusaṃgho samannāgato”ti."
msgstr ""
"May he be blessed with such peace as the Saṅgha of mendicants now enjoys!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.51"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:20.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā, "
"bhikkhusaṃghassa añjaliṃ paṇāmetvā, ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the king bowed to the Buddha, raised his cupped palms toward the "
"Saṅgha, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn2:20.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to the Buddha:"

#. VAR: kañcideva desaṃ → kiñcideva desaṃ lesamattaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:20.3"
msgid "“puccheyyāmahaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ kañcideva desaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I’d like to ask you about a certain point, if you’d take the time to "
"answer.”"

msgctxt "dn2:20.4"
msgid "sace me bhagavā okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn2:20.5"
msgid "“Puccha, mahārāja, yadākaṅkhasī”ti."
msgstr "“Ask what you wish, great king.”"

# Most translators render sippa as "craft". However, the basic meaning of craft is "an activity involving skill in making things by hand". What is meant here is "a paid occupation, especially one that involves prolonged training and a formal qualification." which is "profession". 
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:21.1"
msgid "“Yathā nu kho imāni, bhante, puthusippāyatanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Sir, there are many different professional fields. These include"

# The first set of these is defined as branches of the military at AN 7.67.
#. VAR: nhāpakā → nagāpakā (bj) | nhāpikā (s1-3) | nahāpakā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:21.2"
msgid ""
"hatthārohā assārohā rathikā dhanuggahā celakā calakā piṇḍadāyakā uggā "
"rājaputtā pakkhandino mahānāgā sūrā cammayodhino dāsikaputtā āḷārikā kappakā "
"nhāpakā sūdā mālakārā rajakā pesakārā naḷakārā kumbhakārā gaṇakā muddikā, "
"yāni vā panaññānipi evaṃgatāni puthusippāyatanāni, te diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sandiṭṭhikaṃ sippaphalaṃ upajīvanti;"
msgstr ""
"elephant riders, cavalry, charioteers, archers, bannermen, adjutants, food "
"servers, warrior-chiefs, princes, chargers, great warriors, heroes, leather-"
"clad soldiers, and sons of bondservants. They also include bakers, barbers, "
"bathroom attendants, cooks, garland-makers, dyers, weavers, basket-makers, "
"potters, accountants, finger-talliers, or those following any similar "
"professions. All these live off the fruits of their profession which are "
"apparent in the present life."

#. VAR: pīṇenti → pīnenti (bj)
msgctxt "dn2:21.3"
msgid ""
"te tena attānaṃ sukhenti pīṇenti, mātāpitaro sukhenti pīṇenti, puttadāraṃ "
"sukhenti pīṇenti, mittāmacce sukhenti pīṇenti, samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ "
"dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhapenti sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ."
msgstr ""
"With that they bring happiness and joy to themselves, their parents, their "
"children and partners, and their friends and colleagues. And they establish "
"an uplifting teacher’s offering for ascetics and brahmins that’s conducive "
"to heaven, ripens in happiness, and leads to heaven."

msgctxt "dn2:21.4"
msgid ""
"Sakkā nu kho, bhante, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"paññapetun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Sir, can you point out a fruit of the ascetic life that’s likewise apparent "
"in the present life?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.52"></a>
#. VAR: ti → cāti (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Abhijānāsi no tvaṃ, mahārāja, imaṃ pañhaṃ aññe samaṇabrāhmaṇe pucchitā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Great king, do you recall having asked this question of other ascetics and "
"brahmins?”"

msgctxt "dn2:22.2"
msgid "“Abhijānāmahaṃ, bhante, imaṃ pañhaṃ aññe samaṇabrāhmaṇe pucchitā”ti."
msgstr "“I do, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn2:22.3"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, mahārāja, byākariṃsu, sace te agaru bhāsassū”ti."
msgstr "“If you wouldn’t mind, great king, tell me how they answered.”"

msgctxt "dn2:22.4"
msgid ""
"“Na kho me, bhante, garu, yatthassa bhagavā nisinno, bhagavantarūpo vā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s no trouble when someone such as the Blessed One is sitting here.”"

msgctxt "dn2:22.5"
msgid "“Tena hi, mahārāja, bhāsassū”ti."
msgstr "“Well, speak then, great king.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:23.1"
msgid "3.1. Pūraṇakassapavāda"
msgstr "The Doctrine of Pūraṇa Kassapa"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:24.1"
msgid "“Ekamidāhaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ yena pūraṇo kassapo tenupasaṅkamiṃ;"
msgstr "“One time, sir, I approached Pūraṇa Kassapa"

msgctxt "dn2:24.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā pūraṇena kassapena saddhiṃ sammodiṃ."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn2:24.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, I sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn2:24.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ahaṃ, bhante, pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "and asked him the same question."

msgctxt "dn2:24.5"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bho kassapa, puthusippāyatanāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:24.6"
msgid ""
"hatthārohā assārohā rathikā dhanuggahā celakā calakā piṇḍadāyakā uggā "
"rājaputtā pakkhandino mahānāgā sūrā cammayodhino dāsikaputtā āḷārikā kappakā "
"nhāpakā sūdā mālakārā rajakā pesakārā naḷakārā kumbhakārā gaṇakā muddikā, "
"yāni vā panaññānipi evaṅgatāni puthusippāyatanāni, te diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sandiṭṭhikaṃ sippaphalaṃ upajīvanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:24.7"
msgid ""
"te tena attānaṃ sukhenti pīṇenti, mātāpitaro sukhenti pīṇenti, puttadāraṃ "
"sukhenti pīṇenti, mittāmacce sukhenti pīṇenti, samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ "
"dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhapenti sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:24.8"
msgid ""
"Sakkā nu kho, bho kassapa, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññapetun’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.53"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:25.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, pūraṇo kassapo maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to me:"

msgctxt "dn2:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘karoto kho, mahārāja, kārayato, chindato chedāpayato, pacato pācāpayato "
"socayato, socāpayato, kilamato kilamāpayato, phandato phandāpayato, "
"pāṇamatipātāpayato, adinnaṃ ādiyato, sandhiṃ chindato, nillopaṃ harato, "
"ekāgārikaṃ karoto, paripanthe tiṭṭhato, paradāraṃ gacchato, musā bhaṇato, "
"karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Great king, the one who acts does nothing wrong when they punish, mutilate, "
"torture, aggrieve, oppress, intimidate, or when they encourage others to do "
"the same. They do nothing wrong when they kill, steal, break into houses, "
"plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, "
"commit adultery, and lie."

msgctxt "dn2:25.3"
msgid ""
"Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ "
"maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo."
msgstr ""
"If you were to reduce all the living creatures of this earth to one heap and "
"mass of flesh with a razor-edged chakram, no evil comes of that, and no "
"outcome of evil."

msgctxt "dn2:25.4"
msgid ""
"Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento "
"pacanto pācāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo."
msgstr ""
"If you were to go along the south bank of the Ganges killing, mutilating, "
"and torturing, and encouraging others to do the same, no evil comes of that, "
"and no outcome of evil. "

msgctxt "dn2:25.5"
msgid ""
"Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento yajanto yajāpento, "
"natthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo."
msgstr ""
"If you were to go along the north bank of the Ganges giving and sacrificing "
"and encouraging others to do the same, no merit comes of that, and no "
"outcome of merit."

msgctxt "dn2:25.6"
msgid ""
"Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo’ti."
msgstr ""
"In giving, self-control, restraint, and truthfulness there is no merit or "
"outcome of merit.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:26.1"
msgid ""
"Itthaṃ kho me, bhante, pūraṇo kassapo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno akiriyaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""
"And so, when I asked Pūraṇa Kassapa about the fruits of the ascetic life "
"apparent in the present life, he answered with the doctrine of inaction."

msgctxt "dn2:26.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, ambaṃ vā puṭṭho labujaṃ byākareyya, labujaṃ vā puṭṭho "
"ambaṃ byākareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It was like someone who, when asked about a mango, answered with a "
"breadfruit, or when asked about a breadfruit, answered with a mango."

msgctxt "dn2:26.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, bhante, pūraṇo kassapo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno akiriyaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:26.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:26.5"
msgid ""
"‘kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ apasādetabbaṃ "
"maññeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How could one such as I presume to rebuke an ascetic or brahmin living in "
"my realm?’"

msgctxt "dn2:26.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, pūraṇassa kassapassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ "
"nappaṭikkosiṃ."
msgstr "So I neither approved nor dismissed that statement of Pūraṇa Kassapa."

# Comm explains Anuggaṇhantoti sārato aggaṇhanto. Anikkujjantoti sāravaseneva idaṃ nissaraṇaṃ, ayaṃ paramatthoti hadaye aṭṭhapento. Byañjanaṃ pana tena uggahitañceva nikkujjitañca. This apparently takes uggahita and nikkujjita as synonyms, which is followed by BB, but not by either Rhys Davids or Thanissaro. I can't see how this can be right, elsewhere nikkujjati always means "overturns".
#. VAR: pakkamiṃ → pakkāmiṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: anikkujjanto → anikkujjento (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:26.7"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā anattamano, anattamanavācaṃ anicchāretvā, "
"tameva vācaṃ anuggaṇhanto anikkujjanto uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I was displeased, but did not express my displeasure. Neither accepting what "
"he said nor contradicting it, I got up from my seat and left."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:27.1"
msgid "3.2. Makkhaligosālavāda"
msgstr "The Doctrine of Makkhali Gosāla"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:28.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ yena makkhali gosālo tenupasaṅkamiṃ;"
msgstr "One time, sir, I approached Makkhali Gosāla"

msgctxt "dn2:28.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā makkhalinā gosālena saddhiṃ sammodiṃ."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn2:28.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, I sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn2:28.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ahaṃ, bhante, makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "and asked him the same question."

msgctxt "dn2:28.5"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bho gosāla, puthusippāyatanāni …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:28.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:28.7"
msgid ""
"sakkā nu kho, bho gosāla, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"paññapetun’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.54"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:29.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, makkhali gosālo maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said:"

#. VAR: ahetū → ahetu (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:29.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi, mahārāja, hetu natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṃkilesāya, ahetū apaccayā "
"sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Great king, there is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient "
"beings. Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or condition."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:29.3"
msgid ""
"Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā, ahetū apaccayā sattā "
"visujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings. "
"Sentient beings are purified without cause or condition."

# The first three phrases, with the Magadhan nominative singular in -e, are unique to this passage. Cp AN 6.38: natthi attakāro, natthi parakāro.
msgctxt "dn2:29.4"
msgid ""
"Natthi attakāre, natthi parakāre, natthi purisakāre, natthi balaṃ, natthi "
"vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo."
msgstr ""
"One does not act of one’s own volition, one does not act of another’s "
"volition, one does not act from a person’s volition. There is no power, no "
"energy, no manly strength or vigor."

#. VAR: sukhadukkhaṃ → sukhañca dukkhañca (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn2:29.5"
msgid ""
"Sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā "
"niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedenti."
msgstr ""
"All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack "
"control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, "
"they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth."

#. VAR: mahākappino → mahākappuno (si, pts1)
#. VAR: pavuṭā → paṭuvā (pts1) | sapuṭā (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:29.6"
msgid ""
"Cuddasa kho panimāni yonipamukhasatasahassāni saṭṭhi ca satāni cha ca satāni "
"pañca ca kammuno satāni pañca ca kammāni tīṇi ca kammāni kamme ca aḍḍhakamme "
"ca dvaṭṭhipaṭipadā dvaṭṭhantarakappā chaḷābhijātiyo aṭṭha purisabhūmiyo "
"ekūnapaññāsa ājīvakasate ekūnapaññāsa paribbājakasate ekūnapaññāsa "
"nāgāvāsasate vīse indriyasate tiṃse nirayasate chattiṃsa rajodhātuyo satta "
"saññīgabbhā satta asaññīgabbhā satta nigaṇṭhigabbhā satta devā satta mānusā "
"satta pisācā satta sarā satta pavuṭā satta pavuṭasatāni satta papātā satta "
"papātasatāni satta supinā satta supinasatāni cullāsīti mahākappino "
"satasahassāni, yāni bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ "
"karissanti."
msgstr ""
"There are 1.4 million main wombs, and 6,000, and 600. There are 500 deeds, "
"and five, and three. There are deeds and half-deeds. There are 62 paths, 62 "
"sub-eons, six classes of rebirth, and eight stages in a person’s life. There "
"are 4,900 <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetics, 4,900 wanderers, and 4,900 naked "
"ascetics. There are 2,000 faculties, 3,000 hells, and 36 realms of dust. "
"There are seven percipient embryos, seven non-percipient embryos, and seven "
"embryos without attachments. There are seven gods, seven humans, and seven "
"goblins. There are seven lakes, seven winds, 700 winds, seven cliffs, and "
"700 cliffs. There are seven dreams and 700 dreams. There are 8.4 million "
"great eons through which the foolish and the astute transmigrate before "
"making an end of suffering."

msgctxt "dn2:29.7"
msgid ""
"Tattha natthi “imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā "
"aparipakkaṃ vā kammaṃ paripācessāmi, paripakkaṃ vā kammaṃ phussa phussa "
"byantiṃ karissāmī”ti hevaṃ natthi."
msgstr ""
"And here there is no such thing as this: ‘By this precept or observance or "
"mortification or spiritual life I shall force unripened deeds to bear their "
"fruit, or eliminate old deeds by experiencing their results little by "
"little’—for that cannot be."

msgctxt "dn2:29.8"
msgid ""
"Doṇamite sukhadukkhe pariyantakate saṃsāre, natthi hāyanavaḍḍhane, natthi "
"ukkaṃsāvakaṃse."
msgstr ""
"Pleasure and pain are allotted. Transmigration lasts only for a limited "
"period, so there’s no increase or decrease, no getting better or worse."

msgctxt "dn2:29.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suttaguḷe khitte nibbeṭhiyamānameva paleti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how, when you toss a ball of string, it rolls away unraveling."

msgctxt "dn2:29.10"
msgid ""
"evameva bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ "
"karissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, after transmigrating the foolish and the astute will make "
"an end of suffering.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.55"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:30.1"
msgid ""
"Itthaṃ kho me, bhante, makkhali gosālo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno saṃsārasuddhiṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""
"And so, when I asked Makkhali Gosāla about the fruits of the ascetic life "
"apparent in the present life, he answered with the doctrine of purification "
"through transmigration."

msgctxt "dn2:30.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, ambaṃ vā puṭṭho labujaṃ byākareyya, labujaṃ vā puṭṭho "
"ambaṃ byākareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It was like someone who, when asked about a mango, answered with a "
"breadfruit, or when asked about a breadfruit, answered with a mango."

msgctxt "dn2:30.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, bhante, makkhali gosālo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno saṃsārasuddhiṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:30.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:30.5"
msgid ""
"‘kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ apasādetabbaṃ "
"maññeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How could one such as I presume to rebuke an ascetic or brahmin living in "
"my realm?’"

msgctxt "dn2:30.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, makkhalissa gosālassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ "
"nappaṭikkosiṃ."
msgstr "So I neither approved nor dismissed that statement of Makkhali Gosāla."

msgctxt "dn2:30.7"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā anattamano, anattamanavācaṃ anicchāretvā, "
"tameva vācaṃ anuggaṇhanto anikkujjanto uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I was displeased, but did not express my displeasure. Neither accepting what "
"he said nor contradicting it, I got up from my seat and left."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:31.1"
msgid "3.3. Ajitakesakambalavāda"
msgstr "The Doctrine of Ajita Kesakambala"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:32.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ yena ajito kesakambalo tenupasaṅkamiṃ;"
msgstr "One time, sir, I approached Ajita Kesakambala"

msgctxt "dn2:32.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ajitena kesakambalena saddhiṃ sammodiṃ."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "dn2:32.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, I sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn2:32.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ahaṃ, bhante, ajitaṃ kesakambalaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "and asked him the same question."

msgctxt "dn2:32.5"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bho ajita, puthusippāyatanāni …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:32.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:32.7"
msgid ""
"sakkā nu kho, bho ajita, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"paññapetun’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:33.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, ajito kesakambalo maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said:"

#. VAR: paro loko → paraloko (s1-3)
#. VAR: sammaggatā → samaggagatā (s1-3) | samaggatā (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:33.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi, mahārāja, dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi "
"sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko, "
"natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā, ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā pavedenti."
msgstr ""
"‘Great king, there is no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s "
"no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no "
"obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And "
"there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who "
"describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight."

msgctxt "dn2:33.3"
msgid ""
"Cātumahābhūtiko ayaṃ puriso, yadā kālaṃ karoti, pathavī pathavikāyaṃ anupeti "
"anupagacchati, āpo āpokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, tejo tejokāyaṃ anupeti "
"anupagacchati, vāyo vāyokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, ākāsaṃ indriyāni "
"saṅkamanti."
msgstr ""
"This person is made up of the four primary elements. When they die, the "
"earth in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of earth. The "
"water in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of water. The "
"fire in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of fire. The air "
"in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of air. The faculties "
"are transferred to space."

msgctxt "dn2:33.4"
msgid "Āsandipañcamā purisā mataṃ ādāya gacchanti."
msgstr "Four men with a bier carry away the corpse."

msgctxt "dn2:33.5"
msgid "Yāvāḷāhanā padāni paññāyanti."
msgstr "Their footprints show the way to the cemetery."

msgctxt "dn2:33.6"
msgid "Kāpotakāni aṭṭhīni bhavanti, bhassantā āhutiyo."
msgstr ""
"The bones become bleached. Offerings dedicated to the gods end in ashes."

msgctxt "dn2:33.7"
msgid "Dattupaññattaṃ yadidaṃ dānaṃ."
msgstr "Giving is a doctrine of morons."

msgctxt "dn2:33.8"
msgid "Tesaṃ tucchaṃ musā vilāpo ye keci atthikavādaṃ vadanti."
msgstr ""
"When anyone affirms a positive teaching it’s just baseless, false nonsense."

msgctxt "dn2:33.9"
msgid ""
"Bāle ca paṇḍite ca kāyassa bhedā ucchijjanti vinassanti, na honti paraṃ "
"maraṇā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Both the foolish and the astute are annihilated and destroyed when their "
"body breaks up, and don’t exist after death.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.56"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:34.1"
msgid ""
"Itthaṃ kho me, bhante, ajito kesakambalo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno ucchedaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""
"And so, when I asked Ajita Kesakambala about the fruits of the ascetic life "
"apparent in the present life, he answered with the doctrine of "
"annihilationism."

msgctxt "dn2:34.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, ambaṃ vā puṭṭho labujaṃ byākareyya, labujaṃ vā puṭṭho "
"ambaṃ byākareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It was like someone who, when asked about a mango, answered with a "
"breadfruit, or when asked about a breadfruit, answered with a mango."

msgctxt "dn2:34.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, bhante, ajito kesakambalo sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno ucchedaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:34.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:34.5"
msgid ""
"‘kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ apasādetabbaṃ "
"maññeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How could one such as I presume to rebuke an ascetic or brahmin living in "
"my realm?’"

msgctxt "dn2:34.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, ajitassa kesakambalassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ "
"nappaṭikkosiṃ."
msgstr ""
"So I neither approved nor dismissed that statement of Ajita Kesakambala."

msgctxt "dn2:34.7"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā anattamano anattamanavācaṃ anicchāretvā tameva "
"vācaṃ anuggaṇhanto anikkujjanto uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I was displeased, but did not express my displeasure. Neither accepting what "
"he said nor contradicting it, I got up from my seat and left."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:35.1"
msgid "3.4. Pakudhakaccāyanavāda"
msgstr "The Doctrine of Pakudha Kaccāyana"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:36.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ yena pakudho kaccāyano tenupasaṅkamiṃ;"
msgstr "One time, sir, I approached Pakudha Kaccāyana"

msgctxt "dn2:36.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā pakudhena kaccāyanena saddhiṃ sammodiṃ."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "dn2:36.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, I sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn2:36.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ahaṃ, bhante, pakudhaṃ kaccāyanaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "and asked him the same question."

msgctxt "dn2:36.5"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bho kaccāyana, puthusippāyatanāni …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:36.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:36.7"
msgid ""
"sakkā nu kho, bho kaccāyana, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññapetun’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:37.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, pakudho kaccāyano maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said:"

msgctxt "dn2:37.2"
msgid ""
"‘sattime, mahārāja, kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā "
"esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""
"‘Great king, these seven substances are not made, not derived, not created, "
"without a creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a "
"pillar."

#. VAR: vipariṇamanti → vipariṇāmenti (c1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:37.3"
msgid ""
"Te na iñjanti, na vipariṇamanti, na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti, nālaṃ "
"aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā."
msgstr ""
"They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to "
"cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other."

msgctxt "dn2:37.4"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "dn2:37.5"
msgid "Pathavikāyo, āpokāyo, tejokāyo, vāyokāyo, sukhe, dukkhe, jīve sattame—"
msgstr ""
"The substances of earth, water, fire, air; pleasure, pain, and the soul is "
"the seventh."

msgctxt "dn2:37.6"
msgid ""
"ime satta kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā "
"esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""
"These seven substances are not made, not derived, not created, without a "
"creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar."

msgctxt "dn2:37.7"
msgid ""
"Te na iñjanti, na vipariṇamanti, na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti, nālaṃ "
"aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā."
msgstr ""
"They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to "
"cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other."

msgctxt "dn2:37.8"
msgid ""
"Tattha natthi hantā vā ghātetā vā, sotā vā sāvetā vā, viññātā vā viññāpetā "
"vā."
msgstr ""
"And here there is no-one who kills or who makes others kill; no-one who "
"learns or who educates others; no-one who understands or who helps others "
"understand."

#. VAR: kiñci → kañci (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn2:37.9"
msgid "Yopi tiṇhena satthena sīsaṃ chindati, na koci kiñci jīvitā voropeti;"
msgstr ""
"If you chop off someone’s head with a sharp sword, you don’t take anyone’s "
"life."

#. VAR: sattannaṃ tveva → sattannaṃyeva (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:37.10"
msgid "sattannaṃ tveva kāyānamantarena satthaṃ vivaramanupatatī’ti."
msgstr "The sword simply passes through the gap between the seven substances.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.57"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:38.1"
msgid ""
"Itthaṃ kho me, bhante, pakudho kaccāyano sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno aññena aññaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""
"And so, when I asked Pakudha Kaccāyana about the fruits of the ascetic life "
"apparent in the present life, he answered with something else entirely."

msgctxt "dn2:38.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, ambaṃ vā puṭṭho labujaṃ byākareyya, labujaṃ vā puṭṭho "
"ambaṃ byākareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It was like someone who, when asked about a mango, answered with a "
"breadfruit, or when asked about a breadfruit, answered with a mango."

msgctxt "dn2:38.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, bhante, pakudho kaccāyano sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho "
"samāno aññena aññaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:38.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:38.5"
msgid ""
"‘kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ apasādetabbaṃ "
"maññeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How could one such as I presume to rebuke an ascetic or brahmin living in "
"my realm?’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:38.6"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, pakudhassa kaccāyanassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ "
"nappaṭikkosiṃ, anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā anattamano, anattamanavācaṃ "
"anicchāretvā tameva vācaṃ anuggaṇhanto anikkujjanto uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ."
msgstr ""
"So I neither approved nor dismissed that statement of Pūraṇa Kassapa. I was "
"displeased, but did not express my displeasure. Neither accepting what he "
"said nor contradicting it, I got up from my seat and left."

#. </p><h3>
