msgctxt "dn2:44.5"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bho sañcaya, puthusippāyatanāni …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:44.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:44.7"
msgid ""
"sakkā nu kho, bho sañcaya, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññapetun’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.59"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:45.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said:"

msgctxt "dn2:45.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi paro lokoti iti ce maṃ pucchasi, atthi paro lokoti iti ce me assa, "
"atthi paro lokoti iti te naṃ byākareyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose you were to ask me whether there is another world. If I believed "
"there was, I would say so. "

msgctxt "dn2:45.3"
msgid ""
"Evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi "
"me no."
msgstr ""
"But I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so."

msgctxt "dn2:45.4"
msgid "Natthi paro loko …"
msgstr "Suppose you were to ask me whether there is no other world …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.6"
msgid "atthi ca natthi ca paro loko …"
msgstr "whether there both is and is not another world …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.8"
msgid "nevatthi na natthi paro loko …"
msgstr "whether there neither is nor is not another world …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.9"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.10"
msgid "atthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr "whether there are beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.12"
msgid "natthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr "whether there are no beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.13"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.14"
msgid "atthi ca natthi ca sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr ""
"whether there both are and are not beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.15"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.16"
msgid "nevatthi na natthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr ""
"whether there neither are nor are not beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.17"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.18"
msgid "atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr "whether there is fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.19"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.20"
msgid "natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr "whether there is no fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.21"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.22"
msgid "atthi ca natthi ca sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr ""
"whether there both is and is not fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.23"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.24"
msgid "nevatthi na natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr ""
"whether there neither is nor is not fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.25"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.26"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One exists after death …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.27"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.28"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One doesn’t exist after death …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.29"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.30"
msgid "hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …"

msgctxt "dn2:45.31"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:45.32"
msgid ""
"neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti iti ce maṃ pucchasi, neva hoti "
"na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti iti ce me assa, neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti iti te naṃ byākareyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"whether a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. If I "
"believed there was, I would say so. "

msgctxt "dn2:45.33"
msgid ""
"Evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi "
"me no’ti."
msgstr ""
"But I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:46.1"
msgid ""
"Itthaṃ kho me, bhante, sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"puṭṭho samāno vikkhepaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""
"And so, when I asked Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta about the fruits of the ascetic "
"life apparent in the present life, he answered with evasiveness."

msgctxt "dn2:46.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, ambaṃ vā puṭṭho labujaṃ byākareyya, labujaṃ vā puṭṭho "
"ambaṃ byākareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It was like someone who, when asked about a mango, answered with a "
"breadfruit, or when asked about a breadfruit, answered with a mango."

msgctxt "dn2:46.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho me, bhante, sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"puṭṭho samāno vikkhepaṃ byākāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:46.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:46.5"
msgid "‘ayañca imesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ sabbabālo sabbamūḷho."
msgstr ""
"‘This is the most foolish and stupid of all these ascetics and brahmins!"

msgctxt "dn2:46.6"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ puṭṭho samāno vikkhepaṃ "
"byākarissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"How on earth can he, when asked about the fruits of the ascetic life "
"apparent in the present life, answer with evasiveness?’"

msgctxt "dn2:46.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "I thought:"

msgctxt "dn2:46.8"
msgid ""
"‘kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ apasādetabbaṃ "
"maññeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘How could one such as I presume to rebuke an ascetic or brahmin living in "
"my realm?’"

msgctxt "dn2:46.9"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, sañcayassa belaṭṭhaputtassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ "
"nappaṭikkosiṃ."
msgstr ""
"So I neither approved nor dismissed that statement of Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta."

msgctxt "dn2:46.10"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā anattamano anattamanavācaṃ anicchāretvā tameva "
"vācaṃ anuggaṇhanto anikkujjanto uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I was displeased, but did not express my displeasure. Neither accepting what "
"he said nor contradicting it, I got up from my seat and left."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn2:47.1"
msgid "4. Sāmaññaphala"
msgstr "The Fruits of the Ascetic Life"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:48.1"
msgid "4.1. Paṭhamasandiṭṭhikasāmaññaphala"
msgstr "The First Fruit of the Ascetic Life"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.60"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:49.1"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, bhagavantampi pucchāmi:"
msgstr "And so I ask the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn2:49.2"
msgid "‘yathā nu kho imāni, bhante, puthusippāyatanāni seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Sir, there are many different professional fields. These include"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:49.3"
msgid ""
"hatthārohā assārohā rathikā dhanuggahā celakā calakā piṇḍadāyakā uggā "
"rājaputtā pakkhandino mahānāgā sūrā cammayodhino dāsikaputtā āḷārikā kappakā "
"nhāpakā sūdā mālakārā rajakā pesakārā naḷakārā kumbhakārā gaṇakā muddikā, "
"yāni vā panaññānipi evaṅgatāni puthusippāyatanāni, te diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sandiṭṭhikaṃ sippaphalaṃ upajīvanti, te tena attānaṃ sukhenti pīṇenti, "
"mātāpitaro sukhenti pīṇenti, puttadāraṃ sukhenti pīṇenti, mittāmacce "
"sukhenti pīṇenti, samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhapenti "
"sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ."
msgstr ""
"elephant riders, cavalry, charioteers, archers, bannermen, adjutants, food "
"servers, warrior-chiefs, princes, chargers, great warriors, heroes, leather-"
"clad soldiers, and sons of bondservants. They also include bakers, barbers, "
"bathroom attendants, cooks, garland-makers, dyers, weavers, basket-makers, "
"potters, accountants, finger-talliers, or those following any similar "
"professions. All these live off the fruits of their profession which are "
"apparent in the present life. With that they bring happiness and joy to "
"themselves, their parents, their children and partners, and their friends "
"and colleagues. And they establish an uplifting teacher’s offering for "
"ascetics and brahmins that’s conducive to heaven, ripens in happiness, and "
"leads to heaven."

msgctxt "dn2:49.4"
msgid ""
"Sakkā nu kho, bhante, evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"paññapetun’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Sir, can you point out a fruit of the ascetic life that’s likewise apparent "
"in the present life?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:50.1"
msgid "“Sakkā, mahārāja."
msgstr "“I can, great king."

msgctxt "dn2:50.2"
msgid "Tena hi, mahārāja, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi."
msgstr "Well then, I’ll ask you about this in return, "

msgctxt "dn2:50.3"
msgid "Yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi."
msgstr "and you can answer as you like."

# BB's "ever on the lookout to see that you are satisfied" is not correct, see mukhaṃ ullokentī at MN 79, SN 56.39
#. VAR: kammakāro → kammakaro (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: mukhullokako → mukhullokiko (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:50.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, idha te assa puriso dāso kammakāro pubbuṭṭhāyī "
"pacchānipātī kiṃkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī mukhullokako."
msgstr ""
"What do you think, great king? Suppose you had a person who was a "
"bondservant, a worker. They get up before you and go to bed after you, and "
"are obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely, and gazing up at your "
"face."

msgctxt "dn2:50.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:50.6"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ, vata bho, abbhutaṃ, vata bho, puññānaṃ gati, puññānaṃ vipāko."
msgstr ""
"‘The outcome and result of good deeds is just so incredible, so amazing!"

msgctxt "dn2:50.7"
msgid "Ayañhi rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto manusso;"
msgstr "For this King Ajātasattu is a human being,"

msgctxt "dn2:50.8"
msgid "ahampi manusso."
msgstr "and so am I."

msgctxt "dn2:50.9"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito "
"samaṅgībhūto paricāreti, devo maññe."
msgstr ""
"Yet he amuses himself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation as if he was a god."

msgctxt "dn2:50.10"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ panamhissa dāso kammakāro pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṃkārapaṭissāvī "
"manāpacārī piyavādī mukhullokako."
msgstr ""
"Whereas I’m his bondservant, his worker. I get up before him and go to bed "
"after him, and am obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely, and "
"gazing up at his face."

msgctxt "dn2:50.11"
msgid "So vatassāhaṃ puññāni kareyyaṃ."
msgstr "I should do good deeds."

msgctxt "dn2:50.12"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ochre robes, and go forth "
"from the lay life into homelessness?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:51.1"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyya."
msgstr "After some time, that is what they do."

msgctxt "dn2:51.2"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kāyena saṃvuto vihareyya, vācāya saṃvuto vihareyya, "
"manasā saṃvuto vihareyya, ghāsacchādanaparamatāya santuṭṭho, abhirato "
"paviveke."
msgstr ""
"Having gone forth they’d live restrained in body, speech, and mind, living "
"content with nothing more than food and clothes, delighting in seclusion."

msgctxt "dn2:51.3"
msgid "Tañce te purisā evamāroceyyuṃ:"
msgstr "And suppose your men were to report all this to you."

#. VAR: deva, jāneyyāsi, yo te so puriso → yo te puriso (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:51.4"
msgid ""
"‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, yo te so puriso dāso kammakāro pubbuṭṭhāyī "
"pacchānipātī kiṃkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī mukhullokako;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:51.5"
msgid ""
"so, deva, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:51.6"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kāyena saṃvuto viharati, vācāya saṃvuto viharati, "
"manasā saṃvuto viharati, ghāsacchādanaparamatāya santuṭṭho, abhirato "
"paviveke’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:51.7"
msgid "Api nu tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Would you say to them:"

msgctxt "dn2:51.8"
msgid ""
"‘etu me, bho, so puriso, punadeva hotu dāso kammakāro pubbuṭṭhāyī "
"pacchānipātī kiṃkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī mukhullokako’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Bring that person to me! Let them once more be my bondservant, my worker’?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.61"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:52.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "dn2:52.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho naṃ mayameva abhivādeyyāmapi, paccuṭṭheyyāmapi, āsanenapi "
"nimanteyyāma, abhinimanteyyāmapi naṃ "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi, dhammikampissa "
"rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidaheyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I would bow to them, rise in their presence, and offer them a seat. "
"I’d invite them to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and "
"supplies for the sick. And I’d arrange for their lawful guarding and "
"protection.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:53.1"
msgid ""
"“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, yadi evaṃ sante hoti vā sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ no vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What do you think, great king? If this is so, is there a fruit of the "
"ascetic life apparent in the present life or not?”"

msgctxt "dn2:53.2"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante hoti sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalan”ti."
msgstr "“Clearly, sir, there is.”"

msgctxt "dn2:53.3"
msgid ""
"“Idaṃ kho te, mahārāja, mayā paṭhamaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññattan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This is the first fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the present "
"life, which I point out to you.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:54.1"
msgid "4.2. Dutiyasandiṭṭhikasāmaññaphala"
msgstr "The Second Fruit of the Ascetic Life"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:55.1"
msgid ""
"“Sakkā pana, bhante, aññampi evameva diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññapetun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, can you point out another fruit of the ascetic life that’s "
"likewise apparent in the present life?”"

msgctxt "dn2:55.2"
msgid "“Sakkā, mahārāja."
msgstr "“I can, great king."

msgctxt "dn2:55.3"
msgid "Tena hi, mahārāja, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi."
msgstr "Well then, I’ll ask you about this in return, "

msgctxt "dn2:55.4"
msgid "Yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi."
msgstr "and you can answer as you like."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/a-note-on-karakarako-rasiva-hako/5535
msgctxt "dn2:55.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, idha te assa puriso kassako gahapatiko karakārako "
"rāsivaḍḍhako."
msgstr ""
"What do you think, great king? Suppose you had a person who was a farmer, a "
"householder, a hard worker, someone who builds up their capital."

msgctxt "dn2:55.6"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:55.7"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, puññānaṃ gati, puññānaṃ vipāko."
msgstr ""
"‘The outcome and result of good deeds is just so incredible, so amazing!"

