msgctxt "dn2:56.4"
msgid ""
"‘yagghe, deva, jāneyyāsi, yo te so puriso kassako gahapatiko karakārako "
"rāsivaḍḍhako;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:56.5"
msgid ""
"so deva kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:56.6"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kāyena saṃvuto viharati, vācāya saṃvuto viharati, "
"manasā saṃvuto viharati, ghāsacchādanaparamatāya santuṭṭho, abhirato "
"paviveke’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:56.7"
msgid "Api nu tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "Would you say to them:"

msgctxt "dn2:56.8"
msgid ""
"‘etu me, bho, so puriso, punadeva hotu kassako gahapatiko karakārako "
"rāsivaḍḍhako’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Bring that person to me! Let them once more be a farmer, a householder, a "
"hard worker, someone who builds up their capital’?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:57.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "dn2:57.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho naṃ mayameva abhivādeyyāmapi, paccuṭṭheyyāmapi, āsanenapi "
"nimanteyyāma, abhinimanteyyāmapi naṃ "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi, dhammikampissa "
"rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidaheyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I would bow to them, rise in their presence, and offer them a seat. "
"I’d invite them to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and "
"supplies for the sick. And I’d arrange for their lawful guarding and "
"protection.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:58.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja?"
msgstr "“What do you think, great king? "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:58.2"
msgid "Yadi evaṃ sante hoti vā sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ no vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If this is so, is there a fruit of the ascetic life apparent in the present "
"life or not?”"

msgctxt "dn2:58.3"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante hoti sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalan”ti."
msgstr "“Clearly, sir, there is.”"

msgctxt "dn2:58.4"
msgid ""
"“Idaṃ kho te, mahārāja, mayā dutiyaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ paññattan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This is the second fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the present "
"life, which I point out to you.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn2:59.1"
msgid "4.3. Paṇītatarasāmaññaphala"
msgstr "The Finer Fruits of the Ascetic Life"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:60.1"
msgid ""
"“Sakkā pana, bhante, aññampi diṭṭheva dhamme sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ "
"paññapetuṃ imehi sandiṭṭhikehi sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca "
"paṇītatarañcā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, can you point out a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in "
"the present life which is better and finer than these?”"

msgctxt "dn2:60.2"
msgid "“Sakkā, mahārāja."
msgstr "“I can, great king."

msgctxt "dn2:60.3"
msgid "Tena hi, mahārāja, suṇohi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Well then, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn2:60.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavato "
"paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied the king."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:61.1"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

msgctxt "dn2:61.2"
msgid ""
"“idha, mahārāja, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā "
"devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā."
msgstr ""
"“Consider when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the "
"world, supreme trainer of people, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, "
"blessed."

msgctxt "dn2:61.3"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ "
"sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti."
msgstr ""
"He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and "
"Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and "
"he makes it known to others."

msgctxt "dn2:61.4"
msgid ""
"So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ "
"sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches Dharma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.63"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:62.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule "
"paccājāto."
msgstr ""
"A householder hears that Dharma, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn "
"in some clan. "

msgctxt "dn2:62.2"
msgid "So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati."
msgstr "They gain faith in the Realized One,"

msgctxt "dn2:62.3"
msgid "So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "and reflect:"

msgctxt "dn2:62.4"
msgid "‘sambādho gharāvāso rajopatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā."
msgstr ""
"‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is "
"wide open."

msgctxt "dn2:62.5"
msgid ""
"Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ "
"saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly "
"full and pure, like a polished shell."

msgctxt "dn2:62.6"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ochre robes, and go forth "
"from the lay life into homelessness?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:63.1"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā "
"bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā "
"ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr ""
"After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small "
"family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ochre robes, and go "
"forth from the lay life into homelessness."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
#. VAR: sīlasampanno, indriyesu guttadvāro → bhojane mattaññū (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:64.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno, aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu, kāyakammavacīkammena samannāgato kusalena, parisuddhājīvo "
"sīlasampanno, indriyesu guttadvāro, satisampajaññena samannāgato, santuṭṭho."
msgstr ""
"Once they’ve gone forth, they live restrained in the code of conduct, with "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. They act skillfully "
"by body and speech. They’re purified in livelihood and accomplished in "
"ethical conduct. They guard the sense doors, have mindfulness and "
"situational awareness, and are content."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn2:65.1"
msgid "4.3.1. Sīla"
msgstr "Ethics"

#. </h4><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:66.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahārāja, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant accomplished in ethics?"

msgctxt "dn2:66.2"
msgid "Idha, mahārāja, bhikkhu pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant gives up killing living creatures, renouncing violence "
"and harming. "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:66.3"
msgid ""
"Nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati."
msgstr ""
"They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all creatures."

msgctxt "dn2:66.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:67.1"
msgid ""
"Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, "
"athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati."
msgstr ""
"They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s "
"given. They keep themselves pure by not thieving."

msgctxt "dn2:67.2"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:68.1"
msgid ""
"Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā."
msgstr ""
"They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common "
"practice of sex."

msgctxt "dn2:68.2"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:69.1"
msgid ""
"Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto "
"paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa."
msgstr ""
"They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re "
"honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words."

msgctxt "dn2:69.2"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.64"></a>
#. VAR: Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ → pisuṇāvācaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:70.1"
msgid "Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti;"
msgstr "They give up divisive speech. "

msgctxt "dn2:70.2"
msgid "ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide "
"people against each other. "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:70.3"
msgid "amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā, amūsaṃ bhedāya."
msgstr "  "

#. VAR: samaggarato → samaggarāmo (bj)
#. VAR: anuppadātā → anuppādātā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:70.4"
msgid ""
"Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato "
"samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting "
"in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony."

msgctxt "dn2:70.5"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a>
#. VAR: Pharusaṃ vācaṃ → pharusāvācaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:71.1"
msgid "Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti;"
msgstr "They give up harsh speech. "

#. VAR: tathārūpiṃ → evarūpiṃ (si)
msgctxt "dn2:71.2"
msgid ""
"yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā "
"bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the "
"heart, polite, likable and agreeable to many people."

msgctxt "dn2:71.3"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:72.1"
msgid ""
"Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī "
"atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena "
"sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They give up idle chatter. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in "
"line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which "
"are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn2:72.2"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:73.1"
msgid "Bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti …"
msgstr "They refrain from injuring plants and seeds."

msgctxt "dn2:73.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:73.3"
msgid "ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā."
msgstr ""
"They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at "
"the wrong time."

msgctxt "dn2:73.4"
msgid "Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows."

msgctxt "dn2:73.5"
msgid "Mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"They refrain from beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, "
"fragrance, and makeup."

msgctxt "dn2:73.6"
msgid "Uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "They avoid high and luxurious beds."

msgctxt "dn2:73.7"
msgid "Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "They avoid receiving gold and money,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.8"
msgid "Āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "raw grains,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.9"
msgid "Āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "raw meat,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.10"
msgid "Itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "women and girls,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.11"
msgid "Dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "male and female bondservants,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.12"
msgid "Ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "goats and sheep,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.13"
msgid "Kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "chickens and pigs,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.14"
msgid "Hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "elephants, cows, horses, and mares,"

msgctxt "dn2:73.15"
msgid "Khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "and fields and land."

msgctxt "dn2:73.16"
msgid "Dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "They refrain from running errands and messages;"

msgctxt "dn2:73.17"
msgid "Kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "buying and selling;"

msgctxt "dn2:73.18"
msgid "Tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "falsifying weights, metals, or measures;"

msgctxt "dn2:73.19"
msgid "Ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;"

msgctxt "dn2:73.20"
msgid "Chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence."

msgctxt "dn2:73.21"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn2:74.1"
msgid "Cūḷasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The shorter section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.65"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:75.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in injuring plants and seeds."

msgctxt "dn2:75.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:75.3"
msgid ""
"mūlabījaṃ khandhabījaṃ phaḷubījaṃ aggabījaṃ bījabījameva pañcamaṃ, iti "
"evarūpā bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"These include plants propagated from roots, stems, cuttings, or joints; and "
"those from regular seeds as the fifth. They refrain from such injury to "
"plants and seeds.’"

msgctxt "dn2:75.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:76.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ sannidhikāraparibhogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in storing up goods for their own enjoyment."

msgctxt "dn2:76.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:76.3"
msgid ""
"annasannidhiṃ pānasannidhiṃ vatthasannidhiṃ yānasannidhiṃ sayanasannidhiṃ "
"gandhasannidhiṃ āmisasannidhiṃ, iti vā iti evarūpā sannidhikāraparibhogā "
"paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as food, drink, clothes, vehicles, bedding, "
"fragrance, and material possessions. They refrain from storing up such goods."

msgctxt "dn2:76.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:77.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ visūkadassanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in seeing shows."

msgctxt "dn2:77.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:77.3"
msgid ""
"naccaṃ gītaṃ vāditaṃ pekkhaṃ akkhānaṃ pāṇissaraṃ vetāḷaṃ kumbhathūṇaṃ "
"sobhanakaṃ caṇḍālaṃ vaṃsaṃ dhovanaṃ hatthiyuddhaṃ assayuddhaṃ mahiṃsayuddhaṃ "
"usabhayuddhaṃ ajayuddhaṃ meṇḍayuddhaṃ kukkuṭayuddhaṃ vaṭṭakayuddhaṃ "
"daṇḍayuddhaṃ muṭṭhiyuddhaṃ nibbuddhaṃ uyyodhikaṃ balaggaṃ senābyūhaṃ "
"anīkadassanaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā visūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as dancing, singing, music, performances, and "
"story telling; clapping, gongs, and kettle-drums; art exhibitions and "
"acrobatic displays; battles of elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, goats, "
"rams, chickens and quails; staff-fights, boxing, and wrestling; combat, roll "
"calls of the armed forces, battle-formations, and regimental reviews. They "
"refrain from such shows."

msgctxt "dn2:77.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:78.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in gambling that causes negligence."

msgctxt "dn2:78.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:78.3"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhapadaṃ dasapadaṃ ākāsaṃ parihārapathaṃ santikaṃ khalikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ "
"salākahatthaṃ akkhaṃ paṅgacīraṃ vaṅkakaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulikaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ "
"rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ akkharikaṃ manesikaṃ yathāvajjaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā "
"jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as checkers, draughts, checkers in the air, "
"hopscotch, spillikins, board-games, tip-cat, drawing straws, dice, leaf-"
"flutes, toy ploughs, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, toy "
"bows, guessing words from syllables, and guessing another’s thoughts. They "
"refrain from such gambling."

msgctxt "dn2:78.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.66"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:79.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ uccāsayanamahāsayanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still make use of high and luxurious bedding."

msgctxt "dn2:79.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:79.3"
msgid ""
"āsandiṃ pallaṅkaṃ gonakaṃ cittakaṃ paṭikaṃ paṭalikaṃ tūlikaṃ vikatikaṃ "
"uddalomiṃ ekantalomiṃ kaṭṭissaṃ koseyyaṃ kuttakaṃ hatthattharaṃ assattharaṃ "
"rathattharaṃ ajinappaveṇiṃ kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇaṃ sauttaracchadaṃ "
"ubhatolohitakūpadhānaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as sofas, couches, woolen covers—shag-piled, "
"colorful, white, embroidered with flowers, quilted, embroidered with "
"animals, double- or single-fringed—and silk covers studded with gems, as "
"well as silken sheets, woven carpets, rugs for elephants, horses, or "
"chariots, antelope hide rugs, and spreads of fine deer hide, with a canopy "
"above and red cushions at both ends. They refrain from such bedding."

msgctxt "dn2:79.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:80.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in storing up goods for their own enjoyment."

msgctxt "dn2:80.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: nāḷikaṃ asiṃ → khaggaṃ (bj, pts1) | asiṃ khaggaṃ (s1-3, km) | khaggaṃ
#. asiṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:80.3"
msgid ""
"ucchādanaṃ parimaddanaṃ nhāpanaṃ sambāhanaṃ ādāsaṃ añjanaṃ "
"mālāgandhavilepanaṃ mukhacuṇṇaṃ mukhalepanaṃ hatthabandhaṃ sikhābandhaṃ "
"daṇḍaṃ nāḷikaṃ asiṃ chattaṃ citrupāhanaṃ uṇhīsaṃ maṇiṃ vālabījaniṃ odātāni "
"vatthāni dīghadasāni iti vā iti evarūpā maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogā "
"paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as applying beauty products by anointing, "
"massaging, bathing, and rubbing; mirrors, ointments, garlands, fragrances, "
"and makeup; face-powder, foundation, bracelets, head-bands, fancy walking-"
"sticks or containers, rapiers, parasols, fancy sandals, turbans, jewelry, "
"choweries, and long-fringed white robes. They refrain from such "
"beautification and adornment."

msgctxt "dn2:80.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:81.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in unworthy talk."

#. VAR: janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ → itthikathaṃ purisakathaṃ (bj, s1, s2,
#. pts1) | itthīkathaṃ purisakathaṃ (s3) | itthikathaṃ purisakathaṃ
#. kumārakathaṃ kumārikathaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:81.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathidaṃ– rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ "
"yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ "
"gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ "
"janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ "
"pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ "
"itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānakathāya paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such topics as talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk "
"about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; "
"talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, "
"towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and "
"well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and "
"talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence. They refrain "
"from such unworthy talk."

msgctxt "dn2:81.3"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:82.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ viggāhikakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in arguments."

msgctxt "dn2:82.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:82.3"
msgid ""
"na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ "
"tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi, micchā paṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammā "
"paṭipanno, sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te, pure vacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchā "
"vacanīyaṃ pure avaca, adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahito "
"tvamasi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosīti iti vā iti "
"evarūpāya viggāhikakathāya paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"They say such things as: “You don’t understand this teaching and training. I "
"understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching "
"and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on "
"topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said "
"first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has "
"been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re "
"trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!” They refrain from such "
"argumentative talk."

msgctxt "dn2:82.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.67"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:83.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in running errands and messages."

msgctxt "dn2:83.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:83.3"
msgid ""
"raññaṃ, rājamahāmattānaṃ, khattiyānaṃ, brāhmaṇānaṃ, gahapatikānaṃ, kumārānaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"This includes running errands for rulers, ministers, aristocrats, brahmins, "
"householders, or princes who say: “Go here, go there. Take this, bring that "
"from there.” They refrain from such errands."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:83.4"
msgid ""
"idha gaccha, amutrāgaccha, idaṃ hara, amutra idaṃ āharā’ti iti vā iti "
"evarūpā dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn2:83.5"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:84.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"kuhakā ca honti lapakā ca nemittikā ca nippesikā ca lābhena lābhaṃ "
"nijigīsitāro ca."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in deception, flattery, hinting, and belittling, and "
"using material possessions to pursue other material possessions. They "
"refrain from such deception and flattery."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:84.2"
msgid "Iti evarūpā kuhanalapanā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr "  "

msgctxt "dn2:84.3"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn2:85.1"
msgid "Majjhimasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The middle section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:86.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:86.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:86.3"
msgid ""
"aṅgaṃ nimittaṃ uppātaṃ supinaṃ lakkhaṇaṃ mūsikacchinnaṃ aggihomaṃ dabbihomaṃ "
"thusahomaṃ kaṇahomaṃ taṇḍulahomaṃ sappihomaṃ telahomaṃ mukhahomaṃ "
"lohitahomaṃ aṅgavijjā vatthuvijjā khattavijjā sivavijjā bhūtavijjā "
"bhūrivijjā ahivijjā visavijjā vicchikavijjā mūsikavijjā sakuṇavijjā "
"vāyasavijjā pakkajjhānaṃ saraparittāṇaṃ migacakkaṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes such fields as limb-reading, omenology, divining celestial "
"portents, interpreting dreams, divining bodily marks, divining holes in "
"cloth gnawed by mice, fire offerings, ladle offerings, offerings of husks, "
"rice powder, rice, ghee, or oil; offerings from the mouth, blood sacrifices, "
"palmistry; geomancy for building sites, fields, and cemeteries; exorcisms, "
"earth magic, snake charming, poisons; the crafts of the scorpion, the rat, "
"the bird, and the crow; prophesying life span, chanting for protection, and "
"animal cries. They refrain from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such "
"wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:86.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:87.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:87.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:87.3"
msgid ""
"maṇilakkhaṇaṃ vatthalakkhaṇaṃ daṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ satthalakkhaṇaṃ asilakkhaṇaṃ "
"usulakkhaṇaṃ dhanulakkhaṇaṃ āvudhalakkhaṇaṃ itthilakkhaṇaṃ purisalakkhaṇaṃ "
"kumāralakkhaṇaṃ kumārilakkhaṇaṃ dāsalakkhaṇaṃ dāsilakkhaṇaṃ hatthilakkhaṇaṃ "
"assalakkhaṇaṃ mahiṃsalakkhaṇaṃ usabhalakkhaṇaṃ golakkhaṇaṃ ajalakkhaṇaṃ "
"meṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ kukkuṭalakkhaṇaṃ vaṭṭakalakkhaṇaṃ godhālakkhaṇaṃ "
"kaṇṇikalakkhaṇaṃ kacchapalakkhaṇaṃ migalakkhaṇaṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes reading the marks of gems, cloth, clubs, swords, spears, "
"arrows, weapons, women, men, boys, girls, male and female bondservants, "
"elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, cows, goats, rams, chickens, quails, "
"monitor lizards, rabbits, tortoises, or deer. They refrain from such "
"unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:87.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.68"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:88.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:88.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:88.3"
msgid ""
"raññaṃ niyyānaṃ bhavissati, raññaṃ aniyyānaṃ bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ "
"raññaṃ upayānaṃ bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ apayānaṃ bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ "
"raññaṃ upayānaṃ bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ apayānaṃ bhavissati, "
"abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ jayo bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ parājayo bhavissati, "
"bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ jayo bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ parājayo bhavissati, "
"iti imassa jayo bhavissati, imassa parājayo bhavissati iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes making predictions that the king will march forth or march "
"back; or that our king will attack and the enemy king will retreat, or vice "
"versa; or that our king will triumph and the enemy king will be defeated, or "
"vice versa; and so there will be victory for one and defeat for the other. "
"They refrain from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:88.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:89.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:89.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:89.3"
msgid ""
"candaggāho bhavissati, sūriyaggāho bhavissati, nakkhattaggāho bhavissati, "
"candimasūriyānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, candimasūriyānaṃ uppathagamanaṃ "
"bhavissati, nakkhattānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, nakkhattānaṃ "
"uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, ukkāpāto bhavissati, disāḍāho bhavissati, "
"bhūmicālo bhavissati, devadudrabhi bhavissati, candimasūriyanakkhattānaṃ "
"uggamanaṃ ogamanaṃ saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipāko candaggāho "
"bhavissati, evaṃvipāko sūriyaggāho bhavissati, evaṃvipāko nakkhattaggāho "
"bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, "
"evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ "
"nakkhattānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ nakkhattānaṃ "
"uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipāko ukkāpāto bhavissati, evaṃvipāko "
"disāḍāho bhavissati, evaṃvipāko bhūmicālo bhavissati, evaṃvipāko "
"devadudrabhi bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyanakkhattānaṃ uggamanaṃ "
"ogamanaṃ saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ bhavissati iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes making predictions that there will be an eclipse of the moon, "
"or sun, or stars; that the sun, moon, and stars will be in conjunction or in "
"opposition; that there will be a meteor shower, a fiery sky, an earthquake, "
"thunder; that there will be a rising, a setting, a darkening, a brightening "
"of the moon, sun, and stars. And it also includes making predictions about "
"the results of all such phenomena. They refrain from such unworthy branches "
"of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:89.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.69"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:90.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:90.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:90.3"
msgid ""
"suvuṭṭhikā bhavissati, dubbuṭṭhikā bhavissati, subhikkhaṃ bhavissati, "
"dubbhikkhaṃ bhavissati, khemaṃ bhavissati, bhayaṃ bhavissati, rogo "
"bhavissati, ārogyaṃ bhavissati, muddā, gaṇanā, saṅkhānaṃ, kāveyyaṃ, "
"lokāyataṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes predicting whether there will be plenty of rain or drought; "
"plenty to eat or famine; an abundant harvest or a bad harvest; security or "
"peril; sickness or health. It also includes such occupations as computing, "
"accounting, calculating, poetry, and cosmology. They refrain from such "
"unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:90.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:91.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:91.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:91.3"
msgid ""
"āvāhanaṃ vivāhanaṃ saṃvaraṇaṃ vivaraṇaṃ saṅkiraṇaṃ vikiraṇaṃ subhagakaraṇaṃ "
"dubbhagakaraṇaṃ viruddhagabbhakaraṇaṃ jivhānibandhanaṃ hanusaṃhananaṃ "
"hatthābhijappanaṃ hanujappanaṃ kaṇṇajappanaṃ ādāsapañhaṃ kumārikapañhaṃ "
"devapañhaṃ ādiccupaṭṭhānaṃ mahatupaṭṭhānaṃ abbhujjalanaṃ sirivhāyanaṃ iti vā "
"iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes making arrangements for giving and taking in marriage; for "
"engagement and divorce; and for scattering rice inwards or outwards at the "
"wedding ceremony. It also includes casting spells for good or bad luck, "
"curses to prevent conception, bind the tongue, or lock the jaws; charms for "
"the hands and ears; questioning a mirror, a girl, or a god as an oracle; "
"worshiping the sun, worshiping the Great One, breathing fire, and invoking "
"Siri, the goddess of luck. They refrain from such unworthy branches of "
"knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:91.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:92.1"
msgid ""
"Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:92.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:92.3"
msgid ""
"santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ bhūtakammaṃ bhūrikammaṃ vassakammaṃ vossakammaṃ "
"vatthukammaṃ vatthuparikammaṃ ācamanaṃ nhāpanaṃ juhanaṃ vamanaṃ virecanaṃ "
"uddhaṃvirecanaṃ adhovirecanaṃ sīsavirecanaṃ kaṇṇatelaṃ nettatappanaṃ "
"natthukammaṃ añjanaṃ paccañjanaṃ sālākiyaṃ sallakattiyaṃ dārakatikicchā, "
"mūlabhesajjānaṃ anuppadānaṃ, osadhīnaṃ paṭimokkho iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"This includes rites for propitiation, for fulfilling wishes, for ghosts, for "
"the earth, for rain, for property settlement, and for preparing and "
"consecrating house sites, and those involving rinsing and bathing, and "
"oblations. It also includes administering emetics, purgatives, expectorants "
"and phlegmagogues; administering ear-oils, eye restoratives, nasal medicine, "
"ointments and counter-ointments; surgery with needle and scalpel, treating "
"children, prescribing root medicines, and binding on herbs. They refrain "
"from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "dn2:92.4"
msgid "Idampissa hoti sīlasmiṃ."
msgstr "This pertains to their ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.70"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:93.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ "
"samanupassati, yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in any quarter in "
"regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn2:93.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, rājā khattiyo muddhābhisitto nihatapaccāmitto na "
"kutoci bhayaṃ samanupassati, yadidaṃ paccatthikato;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a king who has defeated his enemies. He sees no danger from his "
"foes in any quarter."

msgctxt "dn2:93.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno na kutoci bhayaṃ "
"samanupassati, yadidaṃ sīlasaṃvarato."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant thus accomplished in ethics sees no danger in "
"any quarter in regards to their ethical restraint."

msgctxt "dn2:93.4"
msgid ""
"So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a "
"blameless happiness inside themselves."

msgctxt "dn2:93.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn2:94.1"
msgid "Mahāsīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The longer section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn2:95.1"
msgid "4.3.2. Samādhi"
msgstr "Immersion"

#. </h4><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:96.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahārāja, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "dn2:96.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahārāja, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up "
"in the features and details."

msgctxt "dn2:96.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhā domanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight was left unrestrained, bad unwholesome qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "dn2:96.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

msgctxt "dn2:96.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:96.6"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "dn2:96.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:96.8"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "dn2:96.9"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:96.10"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "dn2:96.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:96.12"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details. "

msgctxt "dn2:96.13"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhā domanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind was left unrestrained, bad unwholesome qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "dn2:96.14"
msgid ""
"So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr ""
"When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied "
"bliss inside themselves."

msgctxt "dn2:96.15"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant guards the sense doors. "

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.71"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:97.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahārāja, bhikkhu satisampajaññena samannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have mindfulness and situational awareness?"

msgctxt "dn2:97.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahārāja, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite "
"vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite "
"sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite "
"nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

msgctxt "dn2:97.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu satisampajaññena samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has mindfulness and situational awareness."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:98.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahārāja, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant content?"

msgctxt "dn2:98.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahārāja, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena, "
"kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-"
"food to look after the belly."

msgctxt "dn2:98.3"
msgid "So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati."
msgstr "Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things."

msgctxt "dn2:98.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti, sapattabhārova ḍeti;"
msgstr "They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden."

msgctxt "dn2:98.5"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena "
"kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body "
"and alms-food to look after the belly."

msgctxt "dn2:98.6"
msgid "So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati."
msgstr "Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things."

msgctxt "dn2:98.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is content."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:99.1"
msgid ""
"So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena "
"indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato, "
"imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ "
"rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ "
"palālapuñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, "
"this noble mindfulness and situational awareness, and this noble "
"contentment, they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a "
"tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the "
"open air, a heap of straw."

msgctxt "dn2:99.2"
msgid ""
"So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ "
"paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down in the meditation "
"posture with their body erect, and establish mindfulness right there."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:100.1"
msgid ""
"So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, "
"cleansing the mind of desire."

msgctxt "dn2:100.2"
msgid ""
"Byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, "
"byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill "
"will, full of compassion for all creatures, cleansing the mind of ill will."

msgctxt "dn2:100.3"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī, sato sampajāno, "
"thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness "
"and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of "
"dullness and drowsiness."

msgctxt "dn2:100.4"
msgid ""
"Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati, ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, "
"uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, "
"their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse."

msgctxt "dn2:100.5"
msgid ""
"Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati, akathaṅkathī kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about "
"wholesome qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.72"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:101.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojeyya."
msgstr "Suppose a man who has gotten into debt were to apply himself to work,"

msgctxt "dn2:101.2"
msgid "Tassa te kammantā samijjheyyuṃ."
msgstr "and his efforts proved successful."

#. VAR: byantiṃ kareyya → byantīkareyya (bj, s1-3, km) | vyantikareyya (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:101.3"
msgid ""
"So yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni, tāni ca byantiṃ kareyya, siyā cassa uttariṃ "
"avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāya."
msgstr ""
"He would pay off the original loan and have enough left over to support his "
"partner."

msgctxt "dn2:101.4"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn2:101.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe iṇaṃ ādāya kammante payojesiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:101.6"
msgid "Tassa me te kammantā samijjhiṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:101.7"
msgid ""
"Sohaṃ yāni ca porāṇāni iṇamūlāni, tāni ca byantiṃ akāsiṃ, atthi ca me "
"uttariṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ dārabharaṇāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:101.8"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "he’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="82"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:102.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso ābādhiko assa dukkhito bāḷhagilāno;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person who was sick, suffering, gravely ill. They’d lose "
"their appetite and get physically weak."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:102.2"
msgid "bhattañcassa nacchādeyya, na cassa kāye balamattā."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn2:102.3"
msgid "So aparena samayena tamhā ābādhā mucceyya;"
msgstr ""
"But after some time they’d recover from that illness, and regain their "
"appetite and their strength."

msgctxt "dn2:102.4"
msgid "bhattaṃ cassa chādeyya, siyā cassa kāye balamattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:102.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn2:102.6"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe ābādhiko ahosiṃ dukkhito bāḷhagilāno;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: na ca me → nacassa me (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:102.7"
msgid "bhattañca me nacchādesi, na ca me āsi kāye balamattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:102.8"
msgid "Somhi etarahi tamhā ābādhā mutto;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:102.9"
msgid "bhattañca me chādeti, atthi ca me kāye balamattā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:102.10"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="83"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:103.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso bandhanāgāre baddho assa."
msgstr "Suppose a person was imprisoned in a jail."

#. VAR: abbhayena → abbayena (bj, mr) | avyayena (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:103.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena tamhā bandhanāgārā mucceyya sotthinā abbhayena, na cassa "
"kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they were released from jail, safe and sound, with no "
"loss of wealth."

msgctxt "dn2:103.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn2:103.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho pubbe bandhanāgāre baddho ahosiṃ, somhi etarahi tamhā bandhanāgārā "
"mutto sotthinā abbhayena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:103.5"
msgid "Natthi ca me kiñci bhogānaṃ vayo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:103.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.73"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:104.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso dāso assa anattādhīno parādhīno na "
"yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was a bondservant. They belonged to someone else and were "
"unable to go where they wish."

msgctxt "dn2:104.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena tamhā dāsabyā mucceyya attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso "
"yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they were freed from servitude. They’d belong to "
"themselves, an emancipated individual able to go where they wish."

msgctxt "dn2:104.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn2:104.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho pubbe dāso ahosiṃ anattādhīno parādhīno na yenakāmaṅgamo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:104.5"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi tamhā dāsabyā mutto attādhīno aparādhīno bhujisso "
"yenakāmaṅgamo’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:104.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "they’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:105.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ "
"paṭipajjeyya dubbhikkhaṃ sappaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person with wealth and property who was travelling along "
"a desert road, which was perilous, with nothing to eat."

msgctxt "dn2:105.2"
msgid ""
"So aparena samayena taṃ kantāraṃ nitthareyya sotthinā, gāmantaṃ anupāpuṇeyya "
"khemaṃ appaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But after some time they crossed over the desert safely, reaching the "
"neighborhood of a village, a sanctuary free of peril."

msgctxt "dn2:105.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "Thinking about this,"

msgctxt "dn2:105.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho pubbe sadhano sabhogo kantāraddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjiṃ dubbhikkhaṃ "
"sappaṭibhayaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:105.5"
msgid ""
"Somhi etarahi taṃ kantāraṃ nitthiṇṇo sotthinā, gāmantaṃ anuppatto khemaṃ "
"appaṭibhayan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:105.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ labhetha pāmojjaṃ, adhigaccheyya somanassaṃ."
msgstr "he’d be filled with gladness and joy."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:106.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu yathā iṇaṃ yathā rogaṃ yathā bandhanāgāraṃ "
"yathā dāsabyaṃ yathā kantāraddhānamaggaṃ, evaṃ ime pañca nīvaraṇe appahīne "
"attani samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, as long as these five hindrances are not given up inside "
"themselves, a mendicant regards them thus as a debt, a disease, a prison, "
"slavery, and a desert crossing."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="87"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:107.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, yathā āṇaṇyaṃ yathā ārogyaṃ yathā bandhanāmokkhaṃ "
"yathā bhujissaṃ yathā khemantabhūmiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"But when these five hindrances are given up inside themselves, a mendicant "
"regards this as freedom from debt, good health, release from prison, "
"emancipation, and sanctuary."

msgctxt "dn2:107.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahīne attani "
"samanupassati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="88"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:108.1"
msgid ""
"Tassime pañca nīvaraṇe pahīne attani samanupassato pāmojjaṃ jāyati, "
"pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing that the hindrances have been given up in them, gladness springs up. "
"Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, the body "
"becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. And when "
"blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="89"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:109.1"
msgid ""
"So vivicceva kāmehi, vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ "
"vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unwholesome qualities, "
"they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while applying the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn2:109.2"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born "
"of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="90"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.74"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:110.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, dakkho nhāpako vā nhāpakantevāsī vā kaṃsathāle "
"nhānīyacuṇṇāni ākiritvā udakena paripphosakaṃ paripphosakaṃ sanneyya, sāyaṃ "
"nhānīyapiṇḍi snehānugatā snehaparetā santarabāhirā phuṭā snehena, na ca "
"paggharaṇī;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like when a skilled bathroom attendant or their apprentice pours bath "
"powder into a bronze dish, sprinkling it little by little with water. They "
"knead it until the ball of bath powder is soaked and saturated with "
"moisture, spread through inside and out; yet no moisture oozes out."

msgctxt "dn2:110.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena "
"abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato "
"kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion."

msgctxt "dn2:110.3"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="91"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:111.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, mahārāja, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the applying of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and "
"confidence, and unified mind, without applying the mind and keeping it "
"connected. "

msgctxt "dn2:111.2"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="92"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.75"></a>
#. VAR: ubbhidodako → ubbhitodako (s1-3, km, mr)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:112.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, udakarahado gambhīro ubbhidodako tassa nevassa "
"puratthimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na dakkhiṇāya disāya udakassa "
"āyamukhaṃ, na pacchimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na uttarāya disāya "
"udakassa āyamukhaṃ, devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a deep lake fed by spring water. There’s no inlet to the east, "
"west, north, or south, and no rainfall to replenish it from time to time. "

msgctxt "dn2:112.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tamhāva udakarahadā sītā vāridhārā ubbhijjitvā tameva udakarahadaṃ "
"sītena vārinā abhisandeyya parisandeyya paripūreyya paripphareyya, nāssa "
"kiñci sabbāvato udakarahadassa sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa."
msgstr ""
"But the stream of cool water welling up in the lake drenches, steeps, fills, "
"and spreads throughout the lake. There’s no part of the lake that’s not "
"spread through with cool water."

msgctxt "dn2:112.3"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena "
"abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato "
"kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s "
"not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion."

msgctxt "dn2:112.4"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This too, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="93"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:113.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, mahārāja, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato "
"sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains "
"in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and "
"aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss’. "

msgctxt "dn2:113.2"
msgid "‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:113.3"
msgid ""
"So imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti "
"parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with bliss free of rapture. "
"There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="94"></a>
#. VAR: paripphuṭāni → paripphaṭāni (s1-3) | paripphuṭṭhāni (pts1)
#. VAR: nāssa → nassā (bj)
#. VAR: parisannāni → abhisannāni (s2, s3) | abhisandāni parisandāni (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:114.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā "
"appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake "
"saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, tāni yāva caggā yāva ca mūlā "
"sītena vārinā abhisannāni parisannāni paripūrāni paripphuṭāni, nāssa kiñci "
"sabbāvataṃ uppalānaṃ vā padumānaṃ vā puṇḍarīkānaṃ vā sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ "
"assa;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of "
"them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving "
"underwater. From the tip to the root they’re drenched, steeped, filled, and "
"soaked with cool water. There’s no part of them that’s not soaked with cool "
"water."

msgctxt "dn2:114.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti "
"parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa "
"nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body "
"with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread "
"with bliss free of rapture."

msgctxt "dn2:114.3"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This too, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="95"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.76"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:115.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, mahārāja, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, "
"pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, so imameva "
"kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci "
"sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="96"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:116.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso odātena vatthena sasīsaṃ pārupitvā nisinno "
"assa, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa odātena vatthena apphuṭaṃ assa;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like someone sitting wrapped from head to foot with white cloth. There’"
"s no part of the body that’s not spread over with white cloth."

msgctxt "dn2:116.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā "
"pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa "
"parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, they sit spreading their body through with pure bright "
"mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind."

msgctxt "dn2:116.3"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn2:117.1"
msgid "4.3.3. Aṭṭhañāṇa"
msgstr "The Eight Knowledges"

#. </h4><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="97"></a>
#. VAR: So → puna caparaṃ mahārāja bhikkhu so (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:118.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "dn2:118.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "dn2:118.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo "
"odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo;"
msgstr ""
"‘This body of mine is physical. It’s made up of the four primary elements, "
"produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to "
"impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction."

msgctxt "dn2:118.4"
msgid "idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhan’ti."
msgstr "And this consciousness of mine is attached to it, tied to it.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="98"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.77"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:119.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato "
"accho vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, "
"with expert workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all "
"good qualities. "

#. VAR: pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā → pītakaṃ vā lohitakaṃ vā (mr)
msgctxt "dn2:119.2"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssa suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"And it was strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown."

msgctxt "dn2:119.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso hatthe karitvā paccavekkheyya:"
msgstr ""
"And someone with good eyesight were to take it in their hand and examine it:"

msgctxt "dn2:119.4"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho "
"vippasanno anāvilo sabbākārasampanno;"
msgstr ""
"‘This beryl gem is naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, with expert "
"workmanship, transparent, clear, and unclouded, endowed with all good "
"qualities. "

msgctxt "dn2:119.5"
msgid ""
"tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ "
"vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And it’s strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.’"

msgctxt "dn2:119.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte "
"ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "dn2:119.7"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:119.8"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo "
"odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:119.9"
msgid "idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:119.10"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="99"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:120.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte manomayaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimmānāya cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward the creation of a mind-made body."

msgctxt "dn2:120.2"
msgid ""
"So imamhā kāyā aññaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimmināti rūpiṃ manomayaṃ sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ "
"ahīnindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this body they create another body, physical, mind-made, complete in "
"all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="100"></a>
#. VAR: īsikaṃ → isikaṃ (bj, s1-3) | isīkaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: Seyyathā → seyyathāpi (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: pavāheyya → pabbāheyya (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:121.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso muñjamhā īsikaṃ pavāheyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was to draw a reed out from its sheath."

msgctxt "dn2:121.2"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

#. VAR: pavāḷhā’ti → pavālhāti (bj) | pabbāḷhāti (s1, s2, mr) | pabāḷhāti (s3)
msgctxt "dn2:121.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ muñjo, ayaṃ īsikā, añño muñjo, aññā īsikā, muñjamhā tveva īsikā "
"pavāḷhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is the reed, this is the sheath. The reed and the sheath are different "
"things. The reed has been drawn out from the sheath.’"

msgctxt "dn2:121.4"
msgid "Seyyathā vā pana, mahārāja, puriso asiṃ kosiyā pavāheyya."
msgstr "Or suppose a person was to draw a sword out from its scabbard."

msgctxt "dn2:121.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:121.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ asi, ayaṃ kosi, añño asi, aññā kosi, kosiyā tveva asi pavāḷho’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is the sword, this is the scabbard. The sword and the scabbard are "
"different things. The sword has been drawn out from the scabbard.’"

msgctxt "dn2:121.7"
msgid "Seyyathā vā pana, mahārāja, puriso ahiṃ karaṇḍā uddhareyya."
msgstr "Or suppose a person was to draw a snake out from its slough."

msgctxt "dn2:121.8"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:121.9"
msgid "‘ayaṃ ahi, ayaṃ karaṇḍo."
msgstr ""
"‘This is the snake, this is the slough. The snake and the slough are "
"different things. The snake has been drawn out from the slough.’"

#. VAR: ubbhato’ti → uddharito (s1-3, km)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:121.10"
msgid "Añño ahi, añño karaṇḍo, karaṇḍā tveva ahi ubbhato’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn2:121.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte manomayaṃ "
"kāyaṃ abhinimmānāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward the creation of a mind-made body."

msgctxt "dn2:121.12"
msgid ""
"So imamhā kāyā aññaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimmināti rūpiṃ manomayaṃ sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ "
"ahīnindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this body they create another body, physical, mind-made, complete in "
"all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty."

msgctxt "dn2:121.13"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="101"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.78"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:122.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte iddhividhāya cittaṃ abhinīharati "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward psychic power."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:122.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti–  ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, "
"bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti;"
msgstr ""
"They wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and "
"becoming one again;"

msgctxt "dn2:122.3"
msgid ""
"āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati "
"seyyathāpi ākāse;"
msgstr ""
"going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space;"
" "

msgctxt "dn2:122.4"
msgid "pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake;"
msgstr "diving in and out of the earth as if it was water; "

#. VAR: abhijjamāne → abhijjamāno (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn2:122.5"
msgid "udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati seyyathāpi pathaviyā;"
msgstr "walking on water as if it was earth; "

msgctxt "dn2:122.6"
msgid "ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo;"
msgstr "flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird;"

msgctxt "dn2:122.7"
msgid ""
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati;"
msgstr ""
"touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful;"

msgctxt "dn2:122.8"
msgid "yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="102"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.79"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:123.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, dakkho kumbhakāro vā kumbhakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatāya mattikāya yaṃ yadeva bhājanavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ tadeva "
"kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there an expert potter or their apprentice had some well-prepared "
"clay. They could produce any kind of pot that they like."

msgctxt "dn2:123.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathā vā pana, mahārāja, dakkho dantakāro vā dantakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatasmiṃ dantasmiṃ yaṃ yadeva dantavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ tadeva "
"kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Or suppose there an expert ivory-carver or their apprentice had some well-"
"prepared ivory. They could produce any kind of ivory item that they like."

msgctxt "dn2:123.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathā vā pana, mahārāja, dakkho suvaṇṇakāro vā suvaṇṇakārantevāsī vā "
"suparikammakatasmiṃ suvaṇṇasmiṃ yaṃ yadeva suvaṇṇavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya, taṃ "
"tadeva kareyya abhinipphādeyya."
msgstr ""
"Or suppose an expert goldsmith or their apprentice had some well-prepared "
"gold. They could produce any kind of gold item that they like."

msgctxt "dn2:123.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte iddhividhāya "
"cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward psychic power."

msgctxt "dn2:123.5"
msgid "So anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.6"
msgid "ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.7"
msgid ""
"āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati "
"seyyathāpi ākāse;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.8"
msgid "pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.9"
msgid "udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati seyyathāpi pathaviyā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.10"
msgid "ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.11"
msgid ""
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.12"
msgid "yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:123.13"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="103"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:124.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte dibbāya sotadhātuyā cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward clairaudience."

msgctxt "dn2:124.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāti "
"dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre santike ca."
msgstr ""
"With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of "
"sounds, human and divine, whether near or far."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="104"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:125.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso addhānamaggappaṭipanno."
msgstr "Suppose there was a person travelling along the road."

# Compare AN 4.114: bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddānaṃ
msgctxt "dn2:125.2"
msgid "So suṇeyya bherisaddampi mudiṅgasaddampi saṅkhapaṇavadindimasaddampi."
msgstr ""
"They’d hear the sound of drums, clay drums, horns, kettledrums, and tom-toms."

msgctxt "dn2:125.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:125.4"
msgid ""
"‘bherisaddo’ itipi, ‘mudiṅgasaddo’ itipi, ‘saṅkhapaṇavadindimasaddo’ itipi."
msgstr ""
"‘That’s the sound of drums,’ and ‘that’s the sound of clay-drums,’ and ‘that’"
"s the sound of horns, kettledrums, and tom-toms.’"

msgctxt "dn2:125.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte dibbāya "
"sotadhātuyā cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward clairaudience."

msgctxt "dn2:125.6"
msgid ""
"So dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāti "
"dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre santike ca."
msgstr ""
"With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of "
"sounds, human and divine, whether near or far."

msgctxt "dn2:125.7"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="105"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.80"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:126.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte cetopariyañāṇāya cittaṃ abhinīharati "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward comprehending the minds of others."

msgctxt "dn2:126.2"
msgid "So parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti—"
msgstr ""
"They understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having "
"comprehended them with their own mind."

msgctxt "dn2:126.3"
msgid ""
"sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘"
"vītarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, "
"vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, samohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘"
"samohaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītamohaṃ cittan’ti "
"pajānāti, saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘saṅkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, vikkhittaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ ‘vikkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘mahaggataṃ "
"cittan’ti pajānāti, amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘amahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, "
"sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sauttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘"
"anuttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samāhitaṃ cittan’ti "
"pajānāti, asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘asamāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, vimuttaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ ‘vimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti, avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’"
"ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’, and mind without greed "
"as ‘mind without greed’. They understand mind with hate … mind without hate …"
" mind with delusion … mind without delusion … contracted mind … scattered "
"mind … expansive mind … unexpansive mind … mind that is not supreme … mind "
"that is supreme … immersed mind … unimmersed mind … freed mind … They "
"understand unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="106"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.81"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:127.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanajātiko ādāse vā "
"parisuddhe pariyodāte acche vā udakapatte sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ "
"paccavekkhamāno sakaṇikaṃ vā ‘sakaṇikan’ti jāneyya, akaṇikaṃ vā ‘akaṇikan’ti "
"jāneyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments, and they examine their own reflection in a clean bright mirror "
"or a clear bowl of water. If they had a spot they’d know ‘I have a spot,’ "
"and if they had no spots they’d know ‘I have no spots.’"

msgctxt "dn2:127.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte "
"cetopariyañāṇāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
