msgid ""
"Idampi kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

#. </p><h5></h5><p><a class="sc" id="107"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:128.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "dn2:128.2"
msgid "So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "They recollect many kinds of past lives, that is,"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:128.3"
msgid ""
"ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo "
"dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi "
"jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe "
"anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe, ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo "
"evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, "
"so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a "
"thousand, a hundred thousand lives; many eons of the world contracting, many "
"eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. "
"They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like "
"this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that "
"was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn "
"somewhere else. "

msgctxt "dn2:128.4"
msgid ""
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti."
msgstr ""
"There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that "
"was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’"

msgctxt "dn2:128.5"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="108"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.82"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:129.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso sakamhā gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya, tamhāpi "
"gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to leave their home village and go to another village. "
"From that village they’d go to yet another village. And from that village "
"they’d return to their home village."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:129.2"
msgid "So tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgaccheyya."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn2:129.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

#. VAR: agacchiṃ → agañchiṃ (s1-3, km) | agañciṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn2:129.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho sakamhā gāmā amuṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, tatra evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ, evaṃ "
"nisīdiṃ, evaṃ abhāsiṃ, evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ, tamhāpi gāmā amuṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, "
"tatrāpi evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ, evaṃ nisīdiṃ, evaṃ abhāsiṃ, evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ, somhi "
"tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgato’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I went from my home village to another village. There I stood like this, "
"sat like that, spoke like this, or kept silent like that. From that village "
"I went to yet another village. There too I stood like this, sat like that, "
"spoke like this, or kept silent like that. And from that village I returned "
"to my home village.’"

