msgctxt "dn2:132.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, spotless, rid of "
"taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they extend it and project "
"it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn2:132.2"
msgid ""
"So idaṃ dukkhanti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ dukkhasamudayoti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ayaṃ dukkhanirodhoti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice "
"that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "dn2:132.3"
msgid ""
"Ime āsavāti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ āsavasamudayoti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, "
"ayaṃ āsavanirodhoti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn2:132.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ ‘vimuttam’iti "
"ñāṇaṃ hoti, ‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ "
"itthattāyā’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. When freed, they know ‘it is "
"freed’. They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual life has been "
"lived, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="112"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.85"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:133.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, pabbatasaṅkhepe udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that in a mountain glen there was a lake that was transparent, "
"clear, and unclouded. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would "
"see the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming "
"about or staying still."

msgctxt "dn2:133.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha cakkhumā puriso tīre ṭhito passeyya sippisambukampi "
"sakkharakathalampi macchagumbampi carantampi tiṭṭhantampi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:133.3"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn2:133.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo."
msgstr ""
"‘This lake is transparent, clear, and unclouded. And here are the mussel "
"shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying "
"still.’"

msgctxt "dn2:133.5"
msgid ""
"Tatrime sippisambukāpi sakkharakathalāpi macchagumbāpi carantipi "
"tiṭṭhantipī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:133.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahārāja, bhikkhu evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte "
"anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ "
"khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their mind has immersed like this—purified, bright, "
"spotless, rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and motionless—they "
"extend it and project it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn2:133.7"
msgid ""
"‘So idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:133.8"
msgid ""
"‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:133.9"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ ‘vimuttam’iti "
"ñāṇaṃ hoti, ‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ "
"itthattāyā’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn2:133.10"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikaṃ sāmaññaphalaṃ purimehi sandiṭṭhikehi "
"sāmaññaphalehi abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"This, great king, is a fruit of the ascetic life that’s apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than the former ones."

msgctxt "dn2:133.11"
msgid ""
"Imasmā ca pana, mahārāja, sandiṭṭhikā sāmaññaphalā aññaṃ sandiṭṭhikaṃ "
"sāmaññaphalaṃ uttaritaraṃ vā paṇītataraṃ vā natthī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And, great king, there is no other fruit of the ascetic life apparent in the "
"present life which is better and finer than this.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn2:134.1"
msgid "5. Ajātasattuupāsakattapaṭivedanā"
msgstr "Ajātasattu Declares Himself a Lay Follower"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="113"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:135.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When the Buddha had spoken, King Ajātasattu said to him:"

msgctxt "dn2:135.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn2:135.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark  "

msgctxt "dn2:135.4"
msgid "‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there,  "

msgctxt "dn2:135.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn2:135.6"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn2:135.7"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life."

msgctxt "dn2:135.8"
msgid ""
"Accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ "
"pitaraṃ dhammikaṃ dhammarājānaṃ issariyakāraṇā jīvitā voropesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me to "
"take the life of my father, a just and principled king, for the sake of "
"sovereignty."

msgctxt "dn2:135.9"
msgid ""
"Tassa me, bhante bhagavā, accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in "
"future.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="114"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:136.1"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tvaṃ, mahārāja, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ "
"yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ pitaraṃ dhammikaṃ dhammarājānaṃ jīvitā voropesi."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, great king, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and "
"unskillful of you to take the life of your father, a just and principled "
"king, for the sake of sovereignty."

msgctxt "dn2:136.2"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho tvaṃ, mahārāja, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, "
"taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt "
"with it properly, I accept it."

msgctxt "dn2:136.3"
msgid ""
"Vuddhihesā, mahārāja, ariyassa vinaye, yo accayaṃ accayato disvā "
"yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti, āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for "
"what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="115"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:137.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When the Buddha had spoken, King Ajātasattu said to him:"

msgctxt "dn2:137.2"
msgid "“handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti."
msgstr "“Well, now, sir, I must go. I have many duties, and much to do.”"

msgctxt "dn2:137.3"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, great king, go when you’re ready.” "

msgctxt "dn2:137.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then the king, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up "
"from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled him, keeping him on his "
"right, before leaving."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="116"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.86"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:138.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantassa rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa "
"vedehiputtassa bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Soon after the king had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

# Note that these terms are commonly used in the context of keeping sila, eg AN 3.50 etc.
msgctxt "dn2:138.2"
msgid "“khatāyaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā."
msgstr "“The king is broken, mendicants,"

msgctxt "dn2:138.3"
msgid "Upahatāyaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā."
msgstr "he is ruined."

msgctxt "dn2:138.4"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā pitaraṃ dhammikaṃ dhammarājānaṃ jīvitā na "
"voropessatha, imasmiññeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ "
"uppajjissathā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he had not taken the life of his father, a just and principled king, the "
"spotless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma would have arisen in him in that "
"very seat.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="117"></a>
msgctxt "dn2:139.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn2:139.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Uplifted, the mendicants approved of what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn2:140.1"
msgid "Sāmaññaphalasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
